# Contributor Covenant Code of Conduct

## Our Pledge

We as contributors, maintainers, and community members pledge to make participation in this project a respectful, inclusive, and harassment-free experience for everyone.

We are committed to fostering an open and collaborative environment where contributors can work together to build reliable, transparent, and impactful AI-powered supply chain solutions.

## Our Standards

Examples of behavior that contribute to a positive environment include:

* Treating others with respect and professionalism.
* Providing constructive feedback and accepting feedback gracefully.
* Supporting contributors of all experience levels.
* Sharing knowledge and collaborating openly.
* Promoting transparency, reproducibility, and responsible AI practices.

Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

* Harassment, discrimination, or hateful conduct.
* Personal attacks, intimidation, or trolling.
* Publishing private or confidential information without permission.
* Misrepresenting model performance, benchmarks, or research findings.
* Deliberately introducing malicious or misleading code.
* Any conduct that creates a hostile or unwelcoming environment.

## Responsible AI and Data Practices

As this project combines forecasting models, external APIs, and LLM-based analysis, contributors are expected to:

* Prioritize transparency and reproducibility.
* Clearly communicate model limitations and assumptions.
* Avoid misleading claims regarding forecasting accuracy.
* Respect data privacy and licensing requirements.
* Promote responsible and ethical AI development.

## Enforcement Responsibilities

Project maintainers are responsible for clarifying and enforcing community standards and may take appropriate action when necessary.

## Scope

This Code of Conduct applies to all project spaces, including issues, pull requests, discussions, documentation, and community communication channels.

## Enforcement

Instances of unacceptable behavior may be reported to the project maintainers for review and appropriate action.

